The next step is to calculate the value.

$$ \begin{aligned}
FV &= {\$50}\cdot{(1+0.001)^{10}} \\
&=\boxed{\$50.50}
\end{aligned}$$

The bond will be worth $50.50 after the first 10 years.

Now we can compute the formula with the values to consider in this case.

$$ \begin{aligned}
r& = \sqrt[10]{\frac{\$50\cdot2}{\$50}}-1\\
& = \boxed{7.18\%}
\end{aligned}$$

In this case the effective rate of return for the last 10 years is of **7.18%**.
